race.description: Shalaa @ Woodside Park F&M Maiden Plate
race.comment: Plenty of chances but sticking with CASTELLITO (9) who is a big danger on her debut effort. Kicked off in town as a juvenile and after getting back made late ground to finish fifth from the tail out wide. Tipped out again and returns after two jump-outs. Stable is going well and looks a huge chance in this. OLIVIA ROSE (5) is fitter for two runs in and has placed at both. Last time booted up from the inside and knuckled down well but found one better over 1240m at Geelong. Drawn well again and should be in the finish. ELSA OF ARENDELLE (10) was solid fresh then although 11th last time at Ballarat did go back to last from the outside draw and spotted a huge start but came home well. Much better draw this time. TUXEDO MISS (7) has placed at both runs this time in and is among the chances.
